00:24.237 --> 00:26.262
(GRUNTING)

00:26.740 --> 00:28.298
(COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING)

00:42.622 --> 00:45.716
(GRUNTING)

00:47.027 --> 00:50.360
Hey, looks like
that cowboy's a goner.

00:51.098 --> 00:52.588
(GROANING)

01:16.289 --> 01:17.779
(GRUNTING)

01:21.395 --> 01:22.419
Mark Allen.

01:22.496 --> 01:23.520
Chip Woolley.

01:27.134 --> 01:28.260
You from around here?

01:28.402 --> 01:29.528
No. You?

01:40.213 --> 01:41.339
Hey!

01:42.349 --> 01:44.613
Hey, darling.
Listen, if you're not busy...

01:45.419 --> 01:46.408
All right then.

01:46.520 --> 01:48.750
(GRUNTING)

01:56.496 --> 01:58.896
What do you say we finish this
and get the hell out of here?

01:58.965 --> 02:01.490
Yeah. That sounds good.

02:05.172 --> 02:06.833
(GLASS SHATTERING)
Ow!

02:10.009 --> 02:11.375
Whoo!

02:12.412 --> 02:13.606
Been a pleasure.

02:13.680 --> 02:14.772
You can say that again.

02:14.915 --> 02:16.007
All right.

02:26.326 --> 02:28.021
(LAUGHING)

02:28.094 --> 02:30.790
Thanks, man.
You saved my ass.
I owe you one.

02:30.864 --> 02:32.195
Is that you?
That's me.

02:32.265 --> 02:34.233
You ride the circuit?
Bulls. You?

02:34.301 --> 02:36.360
Bareback. I'll see you back
at the grounds.

02:36.436 --> 02:39.928
Nah. No more rodeo for me.
Pop's into oil up in Alaska.

02:42.409 --> 02:44.639
Thinks we're going
to strike it rich.

02:44.711 --> 02:46.576
Yeah, you're gonna freeze
your ass off up there.

02:46.913 --> 02:47.902
Yeah, probably.

02:48.715 --> 02:49.704
Uh-oh.

02:51.084 --> 02:52.551
Take it easy, man.
Yeah, you too.

02:56.089 --> 02:59.718
Hey! Don't go picking
no fights with them grizzlies!

03:00.193 --> 03:01.785
(LAUGHING)

03:03.096 --> 03:04.495
Whoo!

04:54.040 --> 04:55.974
Well, how'd he do?

04:58.144 --> 04:59.702
He's kinda lazy.

05:06.953 --> 05:08.978
Looks like
he's falling asleep.

05:10.223 --> 05:11.850
When is the race?

05:11.992 --> 05:13.619
Sunday.

05:16.363 --> 05:17.830
You know, maybe, uh...

05:17.897 --> 05:19.865
Maybe try some
of those vitamins.

05:20.433 --> 05:21.900
You got it, <i>jefe.</i>

05:26.673 --> 05:32.612
Well, with two claims,
a bowed tendon, and our
biggest owner walking away...

05:33.947 --> 05:36.507
I'd say we in a world of hurt,
little brother.

05:37.384 --> 05:40.785
We don't get
more horses to train,
we gonna be out of business.

05:40.854 --> 05:43.345
Well, we got four running
this week.

05:43.423 --> 05:44.981
Should be favored
on a couple of 'em.

05:45.892 --> 05:48.190
We're 0 for 28 this meet.

05:55.735 --> 05:57.259
We got three seconds.

05:58.738 --> 06:01.366
See... What don't you
understand, huh?

06:02.809 --> 06:05.744
Owners don't wanna run second.

06:05.812 --> 06:07.643
They want their picture taken.

06:08.848 --> 06:11.043
That'd be
in the winner's circle.

06:18.525 --> 06:20.288
Give me another one, Gus.

06:21.861 --> 06:23.829
We ain't running
the tab tonight.

06:27.567 --> 06:30.627
Man, you sure are getting
tight around here.

06:32.605 --> 06:33.970
Huh?

06:41.247 --> 06:42.544
Last one.

06:43.516 --> 06:45.177
You're in my will.

06:46.920 --> 06:48.751
Uh-huh.

06:51.558 --> 06:55.858
So, Chip, you got
any long shots for us?

06:56.396 --> 06:59.422
Oh, you're kidding.
That's all he's ever got.

06:59.499 --> 07:02.900
Last time he won a race,
my wife was a virgin.

07:03.303 --> 07:04.964
(LAUGHING)
Oh.

07:05.038 --> 07:08.007
That's funny,
'cause I heard she still was.

07:08.141 --> 07:09.574
ALL: Oh.

07:09.709 --> 07:11.142
(LAUGHING)

07:24.991 --> 07:26.356
I'm all in.

07:26.993 --> 07:27.982
MAN: Oh ho!

07:32.732 --> 07:34.063
(GROANING)

07:35.268 --> 07:37.293
Looks like we a bit short.

07:38.338 --> 07:41.273
I'll give you the rest
next week, Miguel. Sorry, man.

07:50.850 --> 07:52.112
Hey, there, boys.

07:53.686 --> 07:55.119
Lookee here.

07:57.657 --> 07:58.783
Huh?

07:58.858 --> 08:01.190
Who says gambling don't pay?

08:01.628 --> 08:03.152
(LAUGHING)

08:03.229 --> 08:05.493
Where'd that come from?

08:05.565 --> 08:08.056
That... That right there

08:08.134 --> 08:11.035
is evidence of some
serious card sharking.

08:11.104 --> 08:13.698
Those boys down at Gus's,
they don't know what hit 'em.

08:13.773 --> 08:17.800
I drew two flushes,
two on the river,

08:17.877 --> 08:20.573
and I wiped them suckers out.

08:21.381 --> 08:24.111
Well, we got a race tomorrow
and you can barely stand up.

08:24.184 --> 08:27.381
God! Stop your bitching, Bill!

08:28.121 --> 08:30.089
I won, didn't I?

08:30.156 --> 08:33.852
Our losing streak
is over. You?

08:34.928 --> 08:36.919
You just gotta have
a little faith.

08:37.462 --> 08:38.794
(CROWD CHEERING)

08:38.865 --> 08:41.765
ANNOUNCER: <i>And it's</i>
<i>Faith Be Gone by</i>
<i>a length and a half.</i>

08:53.213 --> 08:54.202
(CHEERING)

08:54.280 --> 08:56.077
<i>Well, you just don't see</i>
<i>that every day, folks.</i>

08:56.149 --> 08:59.209
<i>Down and Dirty</i>
<i>fell to his knees</i>
<i>and still won by five lengths.</i>

09:08.194 --> 09:11.163
<i>And it's another win</i>
<i>by You Gotta Be Kidding Me,</i>

09:11.231 --> 09:13.290
<i>giving him three wins</i>
<i>in a row.</i>

09:13.366 --> 09:17.530
<i>Twist the Night Away got up</i>
<i>for second, Topanga Canyon</i>
<i>rallied nicely for third.</i>

09:18.004 --> 09:20.700
(GROANING)

09:21.641 --> 09:26.044
Don't worry, honey.
It's just a slump.
Everybody has them.

09:26.112 --> 09:27.374
Hmm.

09:27.747 --> 09:29.237
Things will turn around
for you.

09:29.315 --> 09:32.284
Yeah, I don't know, Rosa Lee.
It don't feel like it
this time.

09:32.752 --> 09:34.743
Hmm. You'll see.

09:36.389 --> 09:38.050
REPORTER: (ON TV): <i>It's been</i>
<i>a lackluster year so far,</i>

09:38.124 --> 09:40.024
<i>but sales are beginning</i>
<i>to pick up.</i>

09:40.093 --> 09:43.426
<i>Two more of the highest priced</i>
<i>horses at auction in Ruidoso</i>
<i>were picked up today</i>

09:43.496 --> 09:46.397
<i>by Mark Allen</i>
<i>and his Double Eagle Ranch.</i>

09:46.466 --> 09:48.559
<i>This past Friday,</i>
<i>12 horses were sold...</i>

09:48.635 --> 09:49.966
I know that guy.

09:50.637 --> 09:52.002
What guy?

09:52.138 --> 09:53.537
Mark Allen.

09:54.340 --> 09:57.366
Sounds like he's putting
together a nice string
of horses.

10:35.949 --> 10:37.974
(HORSE NEIGHING)

10:53.066 --> 10:54.795
I don't suppose
you remember me.

10:57.637 --> 10:58.763
Chip Woolley.

11:04.410 --> 11:05.638
I'll be damned.

11:07.580 --> 11:08.808
How could I forget you?

11:08.881 --> 11:10.371
Oh.
(LAUGHING)

11:11.985 --> 11:13.680
I can't believe it.

11:13.753 --> 11:16.881
Charlie, this here's an old
friend of mine, Chip Woolley.

11:16.956 --> 11:19.390
This is Charlie Figueroa,
this is my right-hand man.

11:19.459 --> 11:21.154
Nice to meet ya.
Yeah, likewise.

11:23.730 --> 11:25.527
Well, this is crazy.
Mm-hmm.

11:25.598 --> 11:26.690
How you been?

11:26.833 --> 11:27.891
Good. Real good.

11:28.701 --> 11:31.431
You know, I heard you's back
from Alaska.

11:31.504 --> 11:32.801
Seems you done all right.

11:33.539 --> 11:36.337
Well, there's a lot of oil
up there.

11:38.044 --> 11:40.535
I'll tell you though,
I miss the ponies.

11:40.613 --> 11:43.241
Yeah? Well, the talk
is you got quite a stable.

11:44.550 --> 11:47.348
Yeah, I think we got
a few runners. We will see.

11:47.420 --> 11:48.682
How about you?
What have you been up to?

11:48.755 --> 11:51.383
Well, me and my brother,
we got us a place down
by Sunland.

11:51.457 --> 11:52.822
Yeah?
I've been training some.

11:52.892 --> 11:53.916
Yeah? How's that going?

11:54.060 --> 11:55.049
Not bad.

11:55.561 --> 11:56.858
Win some, lose some.

11:56.996 --> 11:58.258
I hear ya.

12:01.834 --> 12:06.862
You know, you, uh...
You ever need another trainer

12:08.808 --> 12:11.800
or, uh, someone
to watch your back...

12:13.880 --> 12:17.509
Well... I might at that.

12:19.118 --> 12:22.383
Listen, why don't you
stick around tonight?

12:22.455 --> 12:24.184
We got us a little party
going on.

12:24.257 --> 12:25.281
Yeah. Sounds good.

12:25.425 --> 12:26.414
Yeah? Good. Come on.

12:27.660 --> 12:29.651
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

12:34.167 --> 12:35.429
Yeah, you tell it.
You tell it. I'll tell it.

12:35.501 --> 12:36.593
But you tell it
better than me.

12:36.669 --> 12:38.830
So I'm with my crazy
cousin here...
You're gonna tell it anyway.

12:38.905 --> 12:40.964
...at his favorite bar
in Mexico, right?

12:41.040 --> 12:43.008
He's been ordering
four shots of tequila
at a time.

12:43.076 --> 12:45.738
Now, he's drinking two,
throwing the rest on me.

12:45.812 --> 12:49.578
We are liquored up
inside and out. Right?

12:49.649 --> 12:51.913
Kelly's gotta take a leak,
so he gets up.

12:51.984 --> 12:54.111
I gotta go too,
so I follow him into the can.

12:54.187 --> 12:55.381
<i>Bano.</i>

12:55.621 --> 12:58.146
The place is packed.
There's nowhere to go
and I can't wait,

12:58.224 --> 13:02.422
so I start pissing all over
the back of Kelly's jeans.

13:02.495 --> 13:03.484
No, no, no, no, no.

13:03.563 --> 13:06.896
Now, I'm thinking it's funny
as hell until he turns around.

13:07.900 --> 13:08.992
It ain't Kelly.

13:09.068 --> 13:11.002
(LAUGHING)
Shit.

13:11.070 --> 13:13.163
You got a couple of good
shiners that night.
Yes, I did.

13:13.239 --> 13:16.504
A couple of broken ribs, too.
Hey, you're lucky
you ain't dead.

13:18.878 --> 13:20.209
Hey.

13:21.180 --> 13:22.511
Here's my lucky charm.

13:22.648 --> 13:23.979
How you doing, Mark?

13:24.050 --> 13:26.245
I missed seeing you
these last couple of weeks.
Where you been?

13:26.319 --> 13:27.650
I've been at the races.

13:27.787 --> 13:29.118
You're always at the races.

13:29.188 --> 13:31.452
Well, baby girl,
that's the horse business.

13:31.524 --> 13:34.425
Yeah? Well, when do we get
to horse around?

13:34.527 --> 13:35.516
Uh-oh.

13:35.795 --> 13:36.784
Oh.

13:42.568 --> 13:44.763
So, what are we
waiting for, boys?

13:46.439 --> 13:48.873
Ah! I can't get anything
to drop!

13:49.842 --> 13:51.673
You boys still thirsty?

13:51.744 --> 13:52.768
Hell, yeah!

13:52.845 --> 13:53.869
Yes, ma'am.

13:57.583 --> 14:00.347
That's my girl, Sandy.
You're the best, babe.

14:03.389 --> 14:04.413
Sandy?

14:06.425 --> 14:07.790
Who the hell is Sandy?

14:07.860 --> 14:11.557
(CHUCKLING SOFTLY)

14:12.331 --> 14:14.697
I said who the hell is Sandy?

14:17.637 --> 14:19.628
You don't remember my name,
do you?

14:21.240 --> 14:22.332
What?

14:22.942 --> 14:24.068
Do you?

14:26.078 --> 14:27.170
Is it Claire?

14:27.313 --> 14:28.405
(LAUGHING)
Oh, God.

14:29.215 --> 14:30.512
(GLASS SHATTERING)
(LAUGHING)

14:30.583 --> 14:31.948
MARK: Hey, man. Stop!

14:32.285 --> 14:33.411
Ow!

14:33.486 --> 14:35.283
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey!

14:35.688 --> 14:37.519
Wait, stop! Wait!

14:40.193 --> 14:41.217
It's Misty, right?

14:41.294 --> 14:42.352
Oh, you son-of...

14:43.329 --> 14:44.353
All right, it's Connie.

14:44.430 --> 14:45.829
(SCREAMING)

14:45.998 --> 14:47.829
It's Sally and...
Hey!

14:48.701 --> 14:50.259
Stop! Wait!

14:52.705 --> 14:55.230
I'm kidding.
I... I know your...

14:57.977 --> 14:59.410
Tammy?

14:59.478 --> 15:01.412
(SCREAMING)
(GLASS SHATTERING)

15:01.480 --> 15:03.004
MARK: Ah, Lord!

15:04.817 --> 15:06.045
WOMAN: Ugh!

15:09.522 --> 15:10.750
I got this.

15:12.258 --> 15:13.885
Shit...
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

15:20.166 --> 15:23.158
Yeah?
Hey, Mark,
Keith Krupper here.

15:23.569 --> 15:26.800
Sorry to call so late,
but a horse just crossed
my desk.

15:26.872 --> 15:27.861
This just couldn't wait.

15:28.140 --> 15:29.164
Shoot.

15:29.442 --> 15:32.206
He's a
two-year-old thoroughbred,
won four in a row.

15:32.311 --> 15:35.542
You know I race
quarter horses. I got no
interest in thoroughbreds.

15:35.615 --> 15:39.847
He's a stakes winner,
just voted the best
two-year-old in Canada.

15:39.919 --> 15:41.250
Name's Mine That Bird.

15:41.454 --> 15:44.218
<i>His daddy, Birdstone,</i>
<i>won the Belmont.</i>

15:44.323 --> 15:45.381
What's the catch?

15:45.458 --> 15:47.790
He's all American,
bred in Kentucky.

15:48.361 --> 15:51.159
He can't run the big races
in Canada as a three-year-old.

15:51.230 --> 15:52.720
That's crazy.

15:52.798 --> 15:55.995
<i>But the kicker is</i>
<i>he's eligible to run</i>
<i>the Juvenile Breeders' Cup.</i>

15:56.068 --> 15:59.504
A two million dollar race,
the whole world
will be watching.

15:59.572 --> 16:01.437
How much they want for him?

16:01.574 --> 16:03.474
<i>$500,000.</i>

16:03.542 --> 16:05.806
<i>But I might be able</i>
<i>to get them to take four.</i>

16:07.446 --> 16:08.640
You need to see him, Mark.

16:10.082 --> 16:12.642
Tell you what,
I'll send my trainer up
to take a look.

16:13.653 --> 16:14.984
But no promises.

16:15.121 --> 16:16.486
<i>Great.</i>
<i>I'll talk to you soon.</i>

16:30.970 --> 16:32.665
PILOT: Tower, November 3-4...

16:36.876 --> 16:40.676
Welcome, Mr. Woolley.
Please, make yourself at home.

16:41.380 --> 16:42.472
Thank you.

16:48.521 --> 16:51.217
Can I get you anything
to drink before we take off?

16:53.659 --> 16:55.627
Mmm-hmm.

16:58.331 --> 17:01.596
Bird's been real special
for me. He's real special.

17:01.667 --> 17:03.862
Knew what he was supposed
to do from the word go.

17:03.969 --> 17:06.961
I saw you picked him up
at auction for only $9500.

17:07.039 --> 17:10.202
We stole him that night.
Thought he'd go
for a lot more.

17:10.976 --> 17:13.205
Never know where that next
jewel shows up.

17:13.979 --> 17:16.174
Told you he won three stakes
in a row, eh?

17:16.382 --> 17:19.249
Well, not many two-year-olds
put that on their resume.

17:19.318 --> 17:20.683
Then why are you selling him?

17:20.752 --> 17:23.813
Buy low, sell high.
That's what I do.

17:29.929 --> 17:31.123
Uh...

17:31.197 --> 17:32.596
He does this
from time to time.

17:37.503 --> 17:39.698
He usually doesn't go too far.

17:45.544 --> 17:46.602
WOMAN:
Easy, Bird.

17:47.213 --> 17:48.237
MAN:
Come on, you dope.

17:51.917 --> 17:53.009
WOMAN: Easy.

17:53.152 --> 17:54.244
That's it. Come on, Bird.

17:54.320 --> 17:55.753
Kinda small, ain't he?

17:57.390 --> 17:59.221
And a little crooked up front.

17:59.992 --> 18:01.550
So was Seabiscuit.

18:02.161 --> 18:03.150
Come on, buddy.

18:03.229 --> 18:04.287
MAN: Come here, boy.

18:08.834 --> 18:10.665
(WHINNYING)

18:15.875 --> 18:17.604
Sure got a mind of his own.

18:23.149 --> 18:24.673
You seen him
on the track yet?

18:25.351 --> 18:28.218
I don't think
it's worth it, Mark.
<i>Well, you made the trip.</i>

18:28.287 --> 18:30.915
Yeah, but I just...
I don't think
he's what you're after.

18:32.391 --> 18:34.222
He walks funny, for one.

18:36.328 --> 18:39.923
Hey, look, I had braces
on my legs as a kid
'cause I walked funny, too.

18:39.999 --> 18:41.296
Let's give him a try.

18:41.434 --> 18:42.731
Okay.

19:16.435 --> 19:18.232
That was a 46 flat.

19:18.370 --> 19:20.133
What'd I tell ya?

19:21.440 --> 19:22.532
What changed?

19:22.608 --> 19:24.473
<i>You don't even notice</i>
<i>he's crooked when he runs.</i>

19:24.543 --> 19:26.477
<i>The little shit</i>
<i>barely touches the ground.</i>

19:26.545 --> 19:29.810
He's got perfect action,
real professional and

19:30.683 --> 19:31.911
he's fast.

19:32.117 --> 19:33.379
<i>Yeah, but a gelding?</i>

19:34.086 --> 19:36.680
CHIP: Oh, forget about
breeding. This one's a runner.

19:38.023 --> 19:39.820
You sure he's sound?

19:39.892 --> 19:41.951
<i>There's not a pimple</i>
<i>on him, Mark.</i>

19:42.161 --> 19:44.789
Hey, you want this horse.

19:48.901 --> 19:51.631
All right, sit tight.
I'm on my way to Doc's.

19:52.972 --> 19:55.304
MARK: <i>Come on, we always</i>
<i>talked about owning</i>
<i>a thoroughbred together.</i>

19:55.374 --> 19:58.036
Breeders' Cup
is in California in 10 days.

19:58.511 --> 20:00.376
If we wanna do this,
we gotta get moving.

20:00.446 --> 20:02.778
Four hundred seems
like a lot of money.

20:02.848 --> 20:05.442
Hell, if he just runs second,
we got our money back.

20:05.518 --> 20:07.816
And if he don't run second,

20:07.920 --> 20:10.684
we bought ourselves
a very expensive pony.

20:12.057 --> 20:15.584
You know I don't like taking
leaps like this, sight unseen.

20:15.661 --> 20:17.492
He's already won $300,000.

20:18.163 --> 20:19.221
I don't know.

20:20.633 --> 20:23.261
I'll tell you what then.
I'll buy him.

20:24.803 --> 20:28.466
I'll buy him myself.
You like what you see,
I'll cut you in.

20:29.375 --> 20:30.433
(CHUCKLING)

20:32.578 --> 20:34.136
Ah, shit. I'm in.

20:34.947 --> 20:36.005
(SLOSHING)

20:36.081 --> 20:37.981
(LAUGHING)

20:53.966 --> 20:55.991
CHIP: There he is, No. 9.

20:56.702 --> 20:58.294
That's all of him, huh?

20:59.104 --> 21:01.095
He's only two.
He'll grow some.

21:03.108 --> 21:07.306
Well, he'd better hurry up
'cause he's not looking
too good at 24 to 1.

21:08.180 --> 21:11.980
Don't you worry, Doc.
He's gonna do great.

21:12.051 --> 21:14.849
If Chip says he can run,
he can run.

21:16.522 --> 21:20.549
Baffert and the sheik
got the favorite, Midshipman.

21:23.028 --> 21:24.017
Howdy.

21:33.639 --> 21:36.301
DOC: I guess we're gonna
find out what we got
pretty quick.

21:37.209 --> 21:40.645
ANNOUNCER: <i>Last few left</i>
<i>to load, Street Hero goes in.</i>

21:40.713 --> 21:43.147
<i>West Side Bernie</i>
<i>to come take the lineup.</i>

21:43.215 --> 21:44.978
<i>Gate's closed, all set.</i>
(BELL RINGING)

21:45.417 --> 21:47.817
<i>And away they go.</i>

21:47.886 --> 21:51.014
<i>Midshipman, West Side Bernie</i>
<i>broke away well.</i>

21:51.090 --> 21:53.422
<i>Street Hero came out</i>
<i>quickly as well.</i>

21:53.492 --> 21:55.722
<i>Here's Mine That Bird</i>
<i>in the black colors</i>

21:55.794 --> 21:57.625
<i>right there</i>
<i>in the fourth position.</i>

21:57.696 --> 22:02.133
<i>Then we come back to Terrain.</i>
<i>Gallant Son has to go</i>
<i>a little wide into the turn.</i>

22:02.201 --> 22:04.192
<i>In behind there</i>
<i>is Silent Valor</i>

22:04.269 --> 22:06.169
<i>and Munnings races</i>
<i>towards the rear.</i>

22:06.238 --> 22:09.105
<i>The pace is good,</i>
<i>12 lengths from first to last.</i>

22:09.174 --> 22:12.075
I mean, he's in there.
He's doing good.

22:12.144 --> 22:13.168
Yeah.

22:13.245 --> 22:16.373
ANNOUNCER: <i>Now they've settled</i>
<i>in with Mine That Bird</i>
<i>a comfortable fifth,</i>

22:16.448 --> 22:18.348
<i>just four lengths off</i>
<i>the leaders.</i>

22:18.417 --> 22:20.681
<i>Then back</i>
<i>to Pioneer of the Nile.</i>

22:20.753 --> 22:22.380
<i>Bushranger is on the far side.</i>

22:22.454 --> 22:25.651
<i>Terrain giving them</i>
<i>eight lengths start</i>
<i>and then comes Gallant Son.</i>

22:25.724 --> 22:29.490
<i>Behind that Azul Leon,</i>
<i>and Munnings is still towards</i>
<i>the rear.</i>

22:29.561 --> 22:34.021
<i>Into the far turn they go.</i>
<i>And it's Midshipman</i>
<i>still showing the way.</i>

22:45.611 --> 22:46.600
Come on.

22:54.186 --> 22:55.653
Let's go! Let's go!

22:55.721 --> 22:58.884
ANNOUNCER: <i>And Midshipman</i>
<i>has won the Breeders'</i>
<i>Cup Juvenile!</i>

22:58.957 --> 23:01.619
<i>Square Eddie with second,</i>
<i>Street Hero finished third.</i>

23:01.694 --> 23:04.822
<i>Then came Terrain, behind</i>
<i>that Pioneer of the Nile,</i>

23:04.930 --> 23:07.797
<i>and Mine That Bird</i>
<i>finished last.</i>

23:09.168 --> 23:10.635
I'm getting too old for this.

23:10.769 --> 23:12.236
Where's the bar?

23:12.404 --> 23:13.666
Whoo!

23:14.106 --> 23:15.471
(LAUGHING)

23:15.541 --> 23:16.667
Come on!

23:31.757 --> 23:33.418
Why'd you hire him?

23:36.462 --> 23:38.453
Doc, he's only had the horse
a week.

23:41.633 --> 23:46.093
We bought ourselves a champion
and he run dead last.
What's that tell ya?

23:47.139 --> 23:49.664
Bird's never run
on synthetic track before.

23:50.342 --> 23:52.367
It ain't the track, Mark.

23:53.378 --> 23:56.779
This guy's going nowhere.
He's got a terrible record.

23:56.849 --> 23:58.646
Yeah, maybe.

24:00.853 --> 24:03.151
But he's got a great record
with me.

24:07.493 --> 24:10.485
This can't be personal.
We're running a business here.

24:10.562 --> 24:11.722
I know that.

24:12.397 --> 24:15.696
And we've got some
hard decisions to make.

24:16.969 --> 24:19.961
I'm saying three strikes
and he's out.

24:22.841 --> 24:24.570
That's a bit harsh, Doc.

24:31.717 --> 24:32.945
So is losing.

24:42.227 --> 24:45.993
(ANNOUNCER ON COMPUTER):
<i>It's Oconee and Bryden,</i>
<i>continuing to throw it down!</i>

24:46.064 --> 24:49.295
<i>One furlong from home</i>
<i>and on the far outside,</i>

24:49.368 --> 24:51.768
<i>Mine That Bird</i>
<i>is charging hard.</i>

24:51.837 --> 24:54.362
<i>Mine That Bird</i>
<i>has upset Minded...</i>

24:54.439 --> 24:56.270
(CLICKING MOUSE)

24:56.341 --> 24:58.832
(ANNOUNCER ON COMPUTER):
<i>Mine That Bird</i>
<i>is charging hard!</i>

24:58.911 --> 25:02.005
<i>Mine That Bird</i>
<i>has upset Minded</i>
<i>in the final six...</i>

25:02.080 --> 25:03.069
(STOPPING VIDEO)

25:03.148 --> 25:04.206
He comes from off the pace.

25:04.283 --> 25:05.307
Yeah.

25:05.384 --> 25:06.408
He needs to chase somebody.

25:06.485 --> 25:07.474
(PLAYING VIDEO)

25:07.553 --> 25:09.350
(ANNOUNCER ON COMPUTER):
<i>Mine That Bird</i>
<i>is charging hard!</i>

25:09.421 --> 25:13.687
<i>Mine That Bird has upset</i>
<i>Minded in the final sixteenth.</i>

25:15.060 --> 25:16.687
I'll be damned.

25:25.237 --> 25:28.968
You're spoiling Bird,
you know that?
<i>Si.</i>

25:30.042 --> 25:31.600
Hey, hey, gimme that.

26:06.511 --> 26:09.207
(NEIGHING)

26:11.116 --> 26:12.947
(CHUCKLING)

26:20.459 --> 26:22.950
(LAUGHING)

26:24.096 --> 26:25.620
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

27:10.242 --> 27:11.504
Hey.
Here he is right there.

27:12.911 --> 27:13.900
Good luck to you, Case.

27:14.046 --> 27:15.035
Thanks, Doc.

27:15.113 --> 27:17.172
Listen up,
he's a one run horse.

27:17.249 --> 27:20.650
You need to keep him covered
up till the three-eighths
pole, then let him roll.

27:20.719 --> 27:22.778
I don't want him on the lead
till ya hit that wire.

27:22.888 --> 27:23.912
Gotcha.

27:23.989 --> 27:25.320
Here we go, boys.

27:25.857 --> 27:27.222
Here we go.

27:37.102 --> 27:38.535
You gotta look good
in the winner's circle.

27:38.603 --> 27:39.934
Well, let's go.

27:41.239 --> 27:42.638
ANNOUNCER: <i>They make their way</i>
<i>into the stretch and</i>

27:42.708 --> 27:44.835
<i>Mine That Bird now digs in</i>
<i>along the rail</i>

27:44.910 --> 27:46.571
<i>but Scorewithcater</i>
<i>puts his head in front,</i>

27:46.645 --> 27:48.272
<i>down the middle of the track</i>
<i>rallying for the lead.</i>

27:48.647 --> 27:51.411
<i>With only two furlongs</i>
<i>to run...</i>
Come on, Bird.

27:51.483 --> 27:53.280
<i>Smoking Legend</i>
<i>in the white silks</i>
<i>makes his move,</i>

27:53.352 --> 27:54.785
<i>but Mine That Bird</i>
<i>fights back.</i>

27:54.886 --> 27:56.683
<i>Scorewithcater responds as...</i>
Come on!

27:56.755 --> 27:58.052
<i>...the three horses</i>
<i>lay it down.</i>

27:58.123 --> 28:00.353
<i>Scorewithcater gets</i>
<i>the upper hand</i>
<i>two lengths in front.</i>

28:00.425 --> 28:05.260
<i>Mine That Bird now beginning</i>
<i>to tire and Scorewithcater</i>
<i>is just too good today.</i>

28:05.330 --> 28:08.197
<i>Scorewithcater, the winner,</i>
<i>Mine That Bird second,</i>

28:08.266 --> 28:10.291
<i>Smoking Legend</i>
<i>got up for third.</i>

28:10.836 --> 28:12.497
That's not how Bird
wants to run.

28:15.173 --> 28:18.165
Casey made his move
way too soon.
Bird didn't have nothing left.

28:18.243 --> 28:22.270
He shoulda. Ain't like he was
running against much.

28:23.281 --> 28:24.839
Yeah, well, at least
we got second.

28:24.916 --> 28:26.781
That puts us
in the Sunland Derby
next month.

28:26.852 --> 28:28.114
$800,000 to run at.

28:28.253 --> 28:29.515
Yup.

28:30.422 --> 28:31.855
We'll be all right.

28:31.990 --> 28:33.423
Yup.

28:38.797 --> 28:40.162
We're bankrupt.

28:40.465 --> 28:43.957
Bankrupt... Give me a break.
We got $2,000
from the race today.

28:44.036 --> 28:45.264
$2,000?

28:46.371 --> 28:50.205
Auggie's Ranch and Feed,
$2,300, past due.

28:50.876 --> 28:54.471
Miller's Farrier Services,
$2,900, past due.

28:54.546 --> 28:58.880
Rancho Veterinary Services,
$9,000

28:58.950 --> 29:00.281
way past due.

29:00.352 --> 29:04.846
Look, just tell 'em we got
a few more races
coming up this month.

29:04.923 --> 29:06.185
No, no, we don't.

29:06.458 --> 29:09.916
Yeah, we got the starter
on the fifth and we'll win
the maiden claimer easy.

29:09.995 --> 29:12.987
Hutchinson took his last horse
away today.

29:14.599 --> 29:16.794
So did Sanders and Parker.

29:23.575 --> 29:25.304
Bird's all we got.

29:28.547 --> 29:30.071
He's all we need.

29:30.148 --> 29:33.914
You can't hang everything
on one horse, Chip.
You know that!

29:33.985 --> 29:35.885
We're fine!

29:35.954 --> 29:38.616
Bird'll take
the Sunland Derby, you watch.

29:39.891 --> 29:41.756
He'll run 'em off their feet.

29:42.094 --> 29:44.654
(TRUMPETS BLOWING)

29:54.239 --> 29:56.400
ANNOUNCER: <i>With three-eighths</i>
<i>of a mile to go</i>
<i>on the Sunland Derby,</i>

29:56.475 --> 29:57.840
<i>it's Kelly Leak</i>
<i>on the outside,</i>

29:57.909 --> 30:00.605
<i>Mine That Bird on the inside</i>
<i>going nose and nose.</i>

30:03.014 --> 30:05.482
<i>And here comes Scorewithcater,</i>
<i>who moves into third</i>

30:05.550 --> 30:08.678
<i>as Mythical Power, the gray,</i>
<i>moves up on the far outside.</i>

30:08.753 --> 30:12.519
<i>But Kelly Leak with a sudden</i>
<i>burst of speed,</i>
<i>opens up by two lengths.</i>

30:12.591 --> 30:14.559
<i>Mine That Bird</i>
<i>is turning along the rail</i>

30:14.626 --> 30:17.220
<i>as Scorewithcater</i>
<i>and Mythical Power</i>
<i>gain ground.</i>

30:17.295 --> 30:18.785
<i>But it's Kelly Leak</i>
<i>who's gonna win</i>

30:18.864 --> 30:21.162
<i>the Sunland Derby</i>
<i>by two and a half lengths.</i>

30:21.233 --> 30:23.133
<i>Mythical Power getting up</i>
<i>for second,</i>

30:23.201 --> 30:25.169
<i>Scorewithcater hangs on</i>
<i>for the show</i>

30:25.237 --> 30:27.728
<i>and Mine That Bird</i>
<i>fades to fourth.</i>

30:29.774 --> 30:30.866
Fourth?

30:41.520 --> 30:42.544
Good job.

30:42.687 --> 30:43.745
Great day, huh? Great day.

30:46.091 --> 30:49.060
Hey, Casey!
You call that a ride?

30:49.127 --> 30:51.322
You rushed him up there
way too early again.

30:51.396 --> 30:53.626
Look, I told you
he's got one run in him.

30:54.266 --> 30:57.099
You cost me another big race.
You're off the horse!

30:57.169 --> 30:59.535
Fine! You need an excuse,
I got your excuse.

30:59.604 --> 31:00.935
It ain't the horse, it's you!

31:01.439 --> 31:03.498
You can't train worth shit.
Never could.

31:03.575 --> 31:06.066
I don't know why anybody'd
give you a horse
to train in the first place.

31:06.144 --> 31:07.304
You piece of shit.

31:34.606 --> 31:36.267
(CLANGING)

31:39.177 --> 31:40.735
(ENGINE SPUTTERING)

31:45.183 --> 31:46.912
(ENGINE STOPPING)

32:02.400 --> 32:03.924
Mr. Woolley.
Yes, sir.

32:04.002 --> 32:05.970
Your brother came through
surgery just fine.

32:06.338 --> 32:08.135
But the breaks in his leg
are very serious.

32:08.673 --> 32:11.801
There's a plate and 12 screws
holding the bones together.

32:11.876 --> 32:15.141
So he's got to stay off
that leg or it won't
heal properly.

32:15.547 --> 32:19.313
He'll be in recovery another
half an hour.
You can visit with him then.

32:19.384 --> 32:20.851
Thank you, sir.

32:22.721 --> 32:23.949
(DOOR CLOSING)

32:29.160 --> 32:32.891
Chip's gonna have a fit,
if anyone else trains Bird.

32:34.065 --> 32:35.692
That's all he's got.

32:37.602 --> 32:39.502
We'll move him to my place.

32:41.072 --> 32:43.438
I got plenty of folks
that'll help him out.

32:53.885 --> 32:56.046
Sorry, this one didn't go
through either.

32:57.022 --> 33:01.083
Maybe try to put half
on this card

33:01.159 --> 33:02.820
and half on that one.

33:16.374 --> 33:17.363
(GRUNTING)

33:24.015 --> 33:25.004
(NICKERING)

33:25.350 --> 33:26.817
Shh.

33:32.057 --> 33:34.924
You tell anyone I was here
and I'm a dead man.

33:38.163 --> 33:40.324
Yeah, had me
a little accident.

33:43.401 --> 33:46.234
Thought for a minute
I might not see you again.

33:49.841 --> 33:50.967
I know...

33:52.310 --> 33:55.802
I know things ain't exactly
worked out so far,
Bird, but...

33:56.614 --> 33:59.174
Yeah, that ain't your fault.
It's mine.

34:00.752 --> 34:02.242
You know, here I am

34:03.588 --> 34:06.648
expecting you to make it
all happen, and well,

34:07.859 --> 34:09.588
we're supposed to be a team.

34:11.429 --> 34:13.260
I know I ain't been there
for ya.

34:14.132 --> 34:16.157
Heck, I ain't been there
for nobody.

34:22.940 --> 34:23.929
(EXHALING)

34:24.042 --> 34:26.101
I'm sorry
I let you down, Bird.

34:29.179 --> 34:30.373
And, uh...

34:32.484 --> 34:34.975
I'm sorry it took
this to wake me up.

34:35.687 --> 34:37.621
You deserve better, so...

34:38.523 --> 34:40.217
So let's make a deal.

34:43.328 --> 34:47.856
I promise I'll give you
everything I got.

34:49.333 --> 34:53.498
And you, you don't hold back.

34:55.672 --> 34:57.834
We'll do it together
from now on.

34:58.676 --> 35:00.644
(BIRD SNORTING)

35:02.013 --> 35:04.174
Yeah, I know.

35:07.552 --> 35:08.814
Deal?

35:14.526 --> 35:17.893
All right. Okay, then.

35:19.998 --> 35:20.987
Deal.

35:22.367 --> 35:23.595
(NICKERING)

35:37.949 --> 35:38.938
Hmm.

35:42.921 --> 35:44.047
Hey, look.

35:44.589 --> 35:46.250
(CHUCKLING)

36:03.808 --> 36:05.673
(CHUCKLING)

36:22.026 --> 36:23.288
Alex!

36:23.995 --> 36:26.930
Come here a sec!
Somebody I want you to meet.

36:28.867 --> 36:29.856
Hey.

36:29.934 --> 36:30.958
Hey, you made it.

36:31.035 --> 36:32.024
Yeah.

36:37.909 --> 36:40.070
No, not a girl, Mark.

36:43.147 --> 36:44.136
Hey.

36:48.253 --> 36:51.120
Chip, this here's Alex.
Best rider I got.

36:52.190 --> 36:53.919
She's gonna help you out
with Bird.

36:56.361 --> 36:57.419
What?

36:59.531 --> 37:01.863
Well, must of been a hell
of a ride for ya, huh?

37:01.933 --> 37:03.992
Let's get you up to the house,
get you settled in.

37:04.068 --> 37:06.036
Alex, put Bird in the stall
for me?

37:06.371 --> 37:07.463
Sure.

37:09.707 --> 37:14.041
I tell ya,
that Alex sure is something.

37:14.112 --> 37:15.443
You're gonna love her.

37:17.448 --> 37:18.881
DOC: <i>He can barely walk.</i>

37:18.950 --> 37:21.544
How in heck's he gonna train
a racehorse?

37:21.619 --> 37:23.814
I got it all figured out.
Alex is gonna help him.

37:23.888 --> 37:27.984
Alex! Come on, Mark,
I know you like her and all,
but let's face it.

37:28.059 --> 37:31.961
We need a trainer here.
Doc, you gotta give him
a chance.

37:32.764 --> 37:35.232
We already did
and he shot two of 'em.

37:35.300 --> 37:38.895
Bird had two bad rides.
He still almost won.

37:39.604 --> 37:40.764
(GROANING)

37:40.838 --> 37:42.601
Lone Star Derby's coming up quick.
(PHONE VIBRATING)

37:42.674 --> 37:44.141
Bird's never looked better.

37:46.110 --> 37:49.136
Yeah?
MAN: <i>Is Mark Allen there,</i>
<i>please?</i>

37:49.213 --> 37:51.875
Speaking.
<i>Hello, Mr. Allen,</i>
<i>this is Ben Huffman,</i>

37:51.950 --> 37:53.815
<i>racing secretary</i>
<i>at Churchill Downs.</i>

37:53.885 --> 37:54.943
<i>I'm calling to tell you</i>

37:55.019 --> 37:58.079
<i>that Mine That Bird</i>
<i>has qualified to run</i>
<i>in the Kentucky Derby.</i>

37:58.156 --> 38:01.353
That's very funny, Earl.
I'm in a meeting with Doc
right now. I'll call you back.

38:01.426 --> 38:02.450
<i>No, Mr. Allen...</i>

38:02.594 --> 38:05.324
I... I... (CHUCKLING)

38:08.132 --> 38:09.190
Okay.

38:12.170 --> 38:14.001
(PHONE VIBRATING)
Look, I...

38:14.339 --> 38:16.534
Earl, I ain't fooling
with ya, all right?
I'm busy right now.

38:16.608 --> 38:19.338
Mr. Allen,
this really is Ben Huffman,

38:19.410 --> 38:22.243
and your horse really did
qualify for the Derby.

38:23.648 --> 38:24.672
I'm sorry, what?

38:24.749 --> 38:27.616
<i>Your horse really did qualify</i>
<i>for the Derby.</i>

38:27.685 --> 38:28.743
How'd that happen?

38:28.820 --> 38:31.380
Well, based on his stakes
earnings last year in Canada.

38:33.024 --> 38:34.355
The Kentucky Derby?

38:34.492 --> 38:35.789
<i>That's right.</i>

38:39.597 --> 38:41.326
(CHUCKLING)

38:44.202 --> 38:45.692
One for the doctor.

38:45.770 --> 38:46.759
Hmm.

38:47.639 --> 38:49.163
One for the missus.

38:49.307 --> 38:50.865
Thank you.

38:52.910 --> 38:54.844
One for the brains
in the family.

38:54.912 --> 38:56.709
(CHUCKLING)

38:56.848 --> 39:00.284
And one for the cowboy
who's gotta be nuts.

39:00.351 --> 39:01.909
He's been nuts a long time.

39:01.986 --> 39:02.975
Hey.

39:03.054 --> 39:04.043
Three more, bartender.

39:04.122 --> 39:05.783
Hey, Doc, how are you?
Hello, Kel.

39:05.857 --> 39:07.222
Joanne. Hello.
Hi, Daddy.

39:08.092 --> 39:09.650
Good to see you, honey.

39:09.727 --> 39:12.924
Hi, Kevin. Good to see you.
Hi, Kelly.
How you doing, buddy?

39:12.997 --> 39:14.191
Hey, Mom.

39:14.332 --> 39:15.560
You guys look so pretty.

39:16.668 --> 39:17.828
Ladies.
Thank you.

39:19.003 --> 39:20.334
Thank you.

39:20.905 --> 39:21.894
Cousin. You get it?

39:21.973 --> 39:22.962
Thank you, cousin.

39:25.510 --> 39:26.568
All right.

39:27.779 --> 39:30.247
Daddy, a toast.

39:30.581 --> 39:34.108
To your little horse
and a big run!

39:34.185 --> 39:35.209
Yeah.

39:35.286 --> 39:38.119
Well, honey, we ain't exactly
decided we're going yet.

39:38.222 --> 39:42.056
How often do you get invited
to run in the Kentucky Derby!

39:42.126 --> 39:44.822
I know it's exciting,
but we don't belong there.

39:44.896 --> 39:46.557
We can't even win
in New Mexico.

39:46.631 --> 39:48.758
It's a horse race, Dad.
Anything can happen.

39:48.833 --> 39:51.233
I just don't want
to embarrass ourselves.

39:51.302 --> 39:54.362
Oh, Leonard,
so what if you don't win.

39:54.472 --> 39:57.236
It'll be a lot of fun
no matter what happens.

39:57.341 --> 40:01.243
We'll get us those big old
hats and fancy dresses.
Yes!

40:02.747 --> 40:04.738
Think of the mint juleps.

40:04.816 --> 40:06.681
We don't even
have a jockey.

40:06.751 --> 40:09.549
We'll get a new one
when we get there.

40:13.691 --> 40:15.022
Come on, Doc.

40:18.730 --> 40:22.791
May God and Don Julio help us.

40:23.067 --> 40:24.432
(LAUGHING)

40:24.569 --> 40:25.934
(CHEERING)

40:27.605 --> 40:29.505
KELLY:
Kentucky, here we come!

40:30.575 --> 40:33.601
Oh, honey, it's gonna
be wonderful!

40:52.597 --> 40:55.259
You're breaking my heart,
you know that?

41:02.673 --> 41:06.632
Listen, this ain't easy,
man, but

41:07.812 --> 41:09.541
me and Doc had a talk.

41:10.014 --> 41:11.641
We're gonna change things up.

41:13.785 --> 41:15.753
You ain't going
to the Lone Star Derby.

41:18.656 --> 41:20.021
I mean, not now.

41:21.959 --> 41:24.154
Just give me one more shot.

41:24.295 --> 41:25.557
Decision's made.

41:25.663 --> 41:26.789
But Bird'll do good there.

41:26.864 --> 41:30.163
I mean, he's really
coming along.
We could turn this around.

41:30.668 --> 41:32.067
I... I don't know.

41:35.940 --> 41:38.272
You think you finally got
this horse figured out?

41:38.342 --> 41:40.242
Yeah, I do.

41:40.311 --> 41:42.609
Yeah, and how far you think
you can drive on that leg?

41:45.049 --> 41:46.209
Far as you wanna go.

41:46.350 --> 41:47.544
How about Louisville?

41:49.854 --> 41:51.014
Louisville?

41:51.088 --> 41:53.556
Mine That Bird's
running in the Kentucky Derby.

41:54.592 --> 41:55.923
You're kidding me, right?

41:56.561 --> 41:58.222
We entered him this morning.

41:58.529 --> 41:59.928
In the Kentucky Derby?

42:04.368 --> 42:05.699
You got one last shot.

42:05.837 --> 42:07.202
Son of a bitch.

42:07.872 --> 42:09.931
Hey, man! I just bought this.

42:10.208 --> 42:11.470
(LAUGHING)

42:11.542 --> 42:12.770
All right.

42:14.512 --> 42:16.104
Time to tighten up
the screws, buddy.

42:20.885 --> 42:23.911
Holy shit.
(LAUGHING)

42:26.190 --> 42:29.921
Bird, you have it all, buddy.

42:41.539 --> 42:45.031
Take Bird out slow
and gallop him once around.

42:45.109 --> 42:46.940
Good morning to you, too.

43:14.071 --> 43:16.972
You're fighting him.
Ya gotta loosen up,
get him to relax.

43:17.074 --> 43:18.302
I wasn't fighting him.

43:19.443 --> 43:21.570
Take him around again
and give him
a little more rein.

43:21.646 --> 43:24.479
He's not gonna run off
with ya.
I know what I'm doing.

43:25.316 --> 43:26.305
If you knew
what you were doing,

43:26.384 --> 43:28.443
I wouldn't have to be out here
telling you, would I?

43:32.023 --> 43:33.251
Thank you.

43:37.495 --> 43:39.053
(GATE OPENING)

43:39.130 --> 43:40.461
(GATE CLOSING)

44:11.128 --> 44:13.221
When are you letting us
out of this hole?

44:13.698 --> 44:15.222
When I'm good and ready.

44:15.967 --> 44:17.366
Like sometime today?

44:17.501 --> 44:18.866
What, you got a date?

44:19.737 --> 44:21.898
You are such a pain in my...

44:22.306 --> 44:23.295
Oh!

44:26.777 --> 44:28.005
(CHUCKLING)

44:45.830 --> 44:47.627
(NEIGHING)

44:48.699 --> 44:49.688
What was that all about?

44:49.767 --> 44:50.825
What?

44:51.068 --> 44:55.232
"What?" You went 58
and change. It's a workout,
not a race.

44:55.306 --> 44:56.603
He did it easy.

44:58.376 --> 45:01.345
It ain't gonna help us
if he's all used up
before the Derby.

45:01.479 --> 45:03.504
Used up?
What are you talking about?

45:04.348 --> 45:07.715
I'm talking about
working him right.
You don't listen!

45:08.085 --> 45:09.780
The hell I don't.
You don't.

45:09.854 --> 45:12.118
I need a rider
who can take instructions.

45:12.189 --> 45:14.157
You know, I have just about
had it with your shit.

45:14.225 --> 45:17.160
You have been riding my ass
ever since you got here!

45:17.228 --> 45:19.059
You know,
that's another thing.
Keep your ass down!

45:19.130 --> 45:20.188
Keep my ass out of this!

45:20.264 --> 45:22.255
Well, it's a little hard to do
when it blocks the sun.

45:24.268 --> 45:27.863
Fine. Let's see you
ride him, cowboy!

45:41.952 --> 45:43.613
(GRUNTING)

45:53.998 --> 45:56.831
Hey, hey. Ah.

46:00.204 --> 46:01.193
MARK:
Hey, listen up, y'all.

46:03.274 --> 46:06.573
Change of plans.
Alex, you're riding with Chip.

46:06.644 --> 46:08.043
What?
What?

46:08.112 --> 46:10.580
Yeah. There's no way
you're going it alone
on that leg.

46:10.648 --> 46:12.445
You can't handle Bird
by yourself.
Sure I can.

46:12.516 --> 46:14.347
Listen, me and Kelly
will be right behind ya.

46:14.418 --> 46:17.546
Stick with you the whole way.
Like flies to shit.

46:18.456 --> 46:20.754
Charlie, we'll see you
in a couple of days.

46:20.825 --> 46:22.349
I'll have Bird's stall
ready for you

46:22.426 --> 46:23.859
when you get there.
All right.

46:23.928 --> 46:24.952
Kelly!

46:25.029 --> 46:26.018
Yup.

46:27.665 --> 46:29.462
Man, I Iove road trips!

46:44.782 --> 46:47.046
(PANTING)

46:47.384 --> 46:48.851
(GRUNTING)

46:56.026 --> 46:57.254
Do you mind?
Ahhh!

46:58.696 --> 47:00.288
(GRUNTING)

47:04.702 --> 47:06.363
Get off of me!

47:11.175 --> 47:12.472
(HORN HONKING)

47:12.543 --> 47:13.635
Y'all ready?

47:15.479 --> 47:16.810
Ah!

47:17.548 --> 47:18.810
There.

47:18.883 --> 47:20.748
Ugh!
(STARTING ENGINE)

47:23.154 --> 47:25.145
Let's head 'em up,
move 'em out.

47:33.664 --> 47:35.632
(COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)

47:41.405 --> 47:43.873
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)

47:47.178 --> 47:48.907
(COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)

47:58.122 --> 47:59.987
(CLEARING THROAT)

48:00.958 --> 48:03.119
(LOUD MUSIC PLAYING ON HEADPHONES)

48:05.996 --> 48:07.623
(TURNING UP VOLUME)

48:15.139 --> 48:17.334
(TURNING UP VOLUME)

48:28.118 --> 48:32.487
(COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING)
♪ <i>And in your eyes</i>
<i>when we're together</i>

48:34.358 --> 48:38.920
♪ <i>That look says more than</i>
<i>words could ever say</i>

48:41.365 --> 48:47.531
♪ <i>You know I hate to tell you</i>
<i>that I'm leaving</i> ♪

48:47.605 --> 48:50.165
Yeah, like flies to shit.

48:54.144 --> 48:57.636
Don't breathe it in.
Are you kidding me?

49:15.699 --> 49:16.723
Hmm.

49:16.800 --> 49:18.199
Thank you.
You're welcome.

49:24.608 --> 49:25.973
Hey, Bird.

49:31.515 --> 49:36.214
Damn it! I left a bag
in Mark's rig.
My lunch was in there.

49:36.287 --> 49:39.723
Aw, I guess you're gonna have
to eat real food
like the rest of the world.

49:40.324 --> 49:42.019
You call that real food?

49:47.731 --> 49:49.164
It's gonna take two days.

49:50.167 --> 49:51.657
Well, we ain't got two days.

49:52.202 --> 49:55.103
I gotta get the part.
That's gonna take a day.

49:55.506 --> 49:57.531
Then another one to put it in.

49:58.175 --> 49:59.972
That's the best I can do.

50:01.512 --> 50:02.706
Well?

50:04.048 --> 50:07.779
Make sure you tell 'em
we'll be back for Bird
first thing in the morning.

50:07.851 --> 50:09.978
Find out what time
the track opens.

50:10.054 --> 50:11.146
I will.

50:11.221 --> 50:14.987
Make sure that stall
has enough bedding
and that it's dry, too.

50:15.059 --> 50:16.686
Okay, okay, okay, okay.

50:16.760 --> 50:18.387
Oh, make sure he gets
his vitamins.

50:18.462 --> 50:20.623
And put his leg wraps on,
all four of 'em.

50:21.065 --> 50:24.432
I got it already!
Would you just relax
and let me handle this?

50:26.070 --> 50:27.059
Geez.

50:27.137 --> 50:28.126
Hey!

50:28.739 --> 50:31.469
Whatever you do,
do not forget to use
that stall lock.

50:36.747 --> 50:36.814
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

50:36.814 --> 50:39.078
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

50:52.796 --> 50:54.320
Boom!

50:59.403 --> 51:01.530
Don't worry, man.
We're only a day behind ya.

51:01.605 --> 51:04.039
Me and Kelly
are gonna take the bikes.
You and Alex keep going.

51:04.108 --> 51:06.235
We'll catch you in Louisville.
How's Bird?

51:06.677 --> 51:09.544
Oh, good.
He's traveling good.

51:09.613 --> 51:11.410
We got him settled in
at the center.

51:11.482 --> 51:13.848
We'll be back on the road
early in the morning.

51:14.551 --> 51:17.452
And Alex?
(CHUCKLING)
<i>She's still alive.</i>

51:18.122 --> 51:20.886
Hey, where are you?

51:20.958 --> 51:22.482
<i>I'm in Brownfield.</i>

51:22.559 --> 51:23.890
Sounds like a party.

51:24.328 --> 51:27.058
Yeah, well, you know
these little local fillies.

51:28.599 --> 51:30.590
They sure do know
how to be hospitable.

51:32.336 --> 51:33.667
Listen, I gotta go.

51:34.304 --> 51:36.397
<i>We'll holler at you</i>
<i>when we get into town.</i>

51:36.507 --> 51:37.565
Have a great trip.

51:37.641 --> 51:38.630
<i>Oh, yeah, you bet...</i>

51:42.312 --> 51:44.507
See you in a couple days.

51:44.581 --> 51:48.210
You don't expect me to stay
in this hell hole, do you?

51:49.019 --> 51:50.486
What's the matter with it?

51:53.223 --> 51:56.454
What's it gonna be?
By the hour or overnight?

51:57.594 --> 51:58.583
Hmm?

52:01.932 --> 52:03.627
(EXHALING)

52:03.967 --> 52:06.162
(GRUNTING)

52:25.823 --> 52:27.882
(PUMP STARTING)

52:41.238 --> 52:42.899
Oh!

52:45.209 --> 52:46.972
Oh, finally.

52:50.080 --> 52:51.411
(GROANING)

52:57.020 --> 52:58.009
(MOANING)

52:59.423 --> 53:02.153
I see you have
the luxury suite.

53:02.226 --> 53:03.784
What do you want?

53:03.861 --> 53:07.627
I don't suppose you have some
toothpaste I could smear
on my teeth.

53:12.369 --> 53:13.802
(GROANING)

53:15.906 --> 53:16.895
ALEX: Hmm.

53:17.374 --> 53:19.274
Y'all have a nice night.

53:22.145 --> 53:23.134
(DOOR CLOSING)

53:23.280 --> 53:24.338
(SIGHING)

53:29.286 --> 53:30.685
(GRUNTING)

53:32.756 --> 53:34.053
(LAUGHING)

53:34.124 --> 53:35.955
Wow, you look great.

53:37.394 --> 53:38.452
Thank you.

53:39.530 --> 53:40.519
Here.

53:42.199 --> 53:43.757
I got you breakfast.

53:49.106 --> 53:51.973
What in the hell is this?

53:52.543 --> 53:55.569
Yogurt. I'm sure you've never
had it before, but

53:56.380 --> 53:57.711
you're gonna love it.

54:02.953 --> 54:04.716
Hey, thanks for the help.

54:18.168 --> 54:20.762
It says here we're less
than 50 miles out
of Texarkana.

54:20.837 --> 54:22.828
Shouldn't we have turned
north by now?

54:23.574 --> 54:26.441
Jesus, do I have
to do everything?

54:26.510 --> 54:28.102
Let me see that.
Where exactly...

54:28.178 --> 54:30.078
(HORN HONKING)
(TIRES SCREECHING)

54:30.180 --> 54:31.169
(GASPS)

54:32.282 --> 54:33.749
(TIRES SCREECHING)

54:35.953 --> 54:37.215
(TIRE HISSING)

54:40.724 --> 54:42.351
(PANTING)

54:51.401 --> 54:52.561
CHIP: Damn it!

54:53.570 --> 54:54.696
Ow!

54:56.273 --> 54:59.765
What the hell's the matter
with you, huh?
You almost got us killed!

54:59.843 --> 55:02.471
I nearly got us killed?
You're the one
who can't freaking drive!

55:02.546 --> 55:04.537
Well, if you could read a map,
none of this would
have happened!

55:04.615 --> 55:08.107
You nearly drive us
into the grill of an oncoming
truck and it's my fault?

55:08.185 --> 55:09.243
Look at that shit!

55:09.319 --> 55:10.718
Oh, I suppose
that's my fault too!

55:10.787 --> 55:12.550
Well, it sure as hell
ain't mine!

55:12.623 --> 55:13.817
(BIRD NEIGHING)

55:16.293 --> 55:18.853
I got Bird,
you get the spare.

55:19.363 --> 55:20.387
Ow!
Oh!

55:20.464 --> 55:22.022
Jesus, Chip!

55:23.133 --> 55:24.862
And don't get lost.

55:29.306 --> 55:31.035
(COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING)

55:57.434 --> 55:59.493
(MUSIC STOPPING)

56:03.840 --> 56:06.001
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

56:14.451 --> 56:16.009
You ain't from around here,
are you?

56:18.655 --> 56:20.350
I know you ain't
from around here.

56:20.424 --> 56:21.823
I know everyone
from around here.

56:22.993 --> 56:25.723
Come on, let's go dance one,
huh? What do you say?

56:25.796 --> 56:27.354
It's my new favorite song.

56:27.431 --> 56:30.025
♪ <i>Bartender came on over</i>
<i>with a shot of his best</i>

56:30.100 --> 56:32.091
Sure. Let's dance one.

56:32.169 --> 56:33.534
MAN: Well, all right.

56:34.871 --> 56:38.432
♪ <i>She came waltzing round</i>
<i>the corner</i>
<i>"Anybody sittin' here?"</i>

56:38.709 --> 56:41.200
♪ <i>Started takin' off</i>
<i>her glasses and lettin'</i>
<i>down her hair</i>

56:41.278 --> 56:42.370
(BELCHING)

56:42.446 --> 56:43.970
♪ <i>I said, "Thank you</i>
<i>for the drink, ma'am"</i>

56:44.047 --> 56:45.947
MAN: You sure know
how to move.

56:46.383 --> 56:50.649
♪ <i>She said, "There's certain</i>
<i>things a woman</i>
<i>can tell about a man"</i>

56:50.721 --> 56:52.780
MAN: Whoo! Yeah!

56:52.956 --> 56:56.414
♪ <i>Do you like the hard kick</i>
<i>of old Kentucky Bourbon</i>

56:56.493 --> 57:00.452
♪ <i>Or the slow burn</i>
<i>of Tennessee Rye</i>

57:00.530 --> 57:04.022
♪ <i>Just when I thought</i>
<i>I lost her</i>
<i>in petty conversation</i>

57:04.101 --> 57:05.329
♪ <i>She said,</i>
<i>"Slide over and kiss me"</i>

57:05.402 --> 57:07.233
You smell good. Good.

57:07.304 --> 57:09.932
♪ <i>"I got more than whiskey</i>
<i>in mind"</i>

57:10.907 --> 57:12.397
Hmm, hmm, hmm.

57:12.476 --> 57:13.670
Come here.

57:15.679 --> 57:16.668
Oh.

57:16.847 --> 57:18.144
Stop it.

57:18.215 --> 57:20.115
Come here.
You know you want it.

57:20.584 --> 57:22.313
You love this.
I said stop it!

57:22.786 --> 57:24.185
Let her go.

57:24.788 --> 57:26.346
What's wrong, girl?
You know you want it.

57:26.623 --> 57:28.147
I said let her go.

57:29.526 --> 57:31.153
You ain't from around here,
are you?

57:31.962 --> 57:33.054
So why don't you...

57:33.130 --> 57:34.119
(GROANING)

57:35.599 --> 57:36.588
(GROWLING)

57:41.138 --> 57:42.662
(THUDDING)

57:43.707 --> 57:44.765
CHIP: Come on!

57:45.976 --> 57:47.568
(GROANING)

57:47.944 --> 57:49.969
♪ <i>I got more than whiskey</i>
<i>in mind</i> ♪

57:52.115 --> 57:53.548
I'm really sorry.

57:58.622 --> 57:59.953
(EXHALING)

58:28.351 --> 58:29.978
Did you get some sleep?

58:30.821 --> 58:32.083
Yeah. You?

58:32.222 --> 58:33.484
Yeah.

58:35.792 --> 58:37.350
(EXHALING)

58:45.368 --> 58:48.599
We'd better get going.
Bird's waiting.

59:04.855 --> 59:06.152
(LAUGHING)

59:16.800 --> 59:18.529
Whoo!

59:28.411 --> 59:30.072
How'd you get into racing?

59:30.814 --> 59:32.008
My dad.

59:33.183 --> 59:35.413
He always found a racetrack
wherever we were stationed

59:35.485 --> 59:36.713
so he could play the ponies.

59:39.155 --> 59:42.022
I remember the first time
I saw racehorses run.

59:44.361 --> 59:46.022
It's like they had wings.

59:49.199 --> 59:51.030
I'd stand at the rail,

59:52.168 --> 59:54.636
try to imagine what it
felt like to fly like that.

59:58.441 --> 01:00:01.171
It nearly killed me
when we had to move again.

01:00:03.446 --> 01:00:05.380
But I swore
I'd come back someday.

01:00:05.448 --> 01:00:07.916
I finally did it
a few months ago.

01:00:07.984 --> 01:00:10.953
That's when I met Mark.
He heard I needed a job
and he hired me.

01:00:14.057 --> 01:00:18.426
I love being around horses.
Especially when I get to ride.

01:00:21.264 --> 01:00:23.164
For me there's
nothing like it.

01:00:24.034 --> 01:00:26.093
Yeah, they get in your blood.

01:00:26.903 --> 01:00:28.336
That's for sure.

01:00:31.141 --> 01:00:32.802
What are his chances?

01:00:35.612 --> 01:00:37.273
Not too good.

01:00:38.882 --> 01:00:40.474
Then why are you doing this?

01:00:47.557 --> 01:00:52.460
I have run a lot of horses
for a lot of people and

01:00:53.596 --> 01:00:56.588
we didn't always
come out ahead,
but we paid the bills.

01:00:58.368 --> 01:00:59.699
It seemed good enough.

01:01:00.971 --> 01:01:03.337
And then Bird come along.

01:01:03.406 --> 01:01:07.137
Boy, he made a dreamer
out of me.
Out of all of us.

01:01:08.411 --> 01:01:13.178
We got a chance
to be a part of something
truly great.

01:01:13.984 --> 01:01:15.975
To be the best there is.

01:01:17.921 --> 01:01:19.821
Maybe we'll look stupid
to some,

01:01:21.758 --> 01:01:24.659
but life ain't worth much
if all you do is play it safe.

01:01:25.295 --> 01:01:29.163
It's about being out there,

01:01:30.133 --> 01:01:31.760
taking chances.

01:01:37.107 --> 01:01:38.301
Well,

01:01:39.409 --> 01:01:42.674
at least we'll know we tried.
We gave it everything we got.

01:01:48.251 --> 01:01:49.650
(GRUNTING)

01:01:55.959 --> 01:01:57.449
You ready to go, Bird?

01:01:57.527 --> 01:01:58.721
(SNORTING)

01:01:59.029 --> 01:02:00.997
I think that's a yes.

01:02:25.789 --> 01:02:28.280
You must be the guys
from New Mexico.

01:02:28.358 --> 01:02:31.293
Wondered when you were
gonna get here.
Yeah, so did we.

01:02:32.062 --> 01:02:35.395
Well, not many folks
drive their Derby horses
cross country.

01:02:37.300 --> 01:02:38.767
Mind if I have a look?

01:02:38.902 --> 01:02:40.369
Be my guest.

01:02:51.147 --> 01:02:52.944
Not much to him, huh?

01:02:54.684 --> 01:02:56.083
Looks can be deceiving.

01:02:56.219 --> 01:02:57.618
You got that right.

01:02:58.088 --> 01:03:00.613
Well, good luck to you

01:03:00.690 --> 01:03:02.214
and welcome
to Churchill Downs.

01:03:02.892 --> 01:03:04.052
Thank you.
(STARTING ENGINE)

01:03:55.145 --> 01:03:58.308
That's Join in the Dance.
He'll have a lot of speed.

01:03:59.282 --> 01:04:01.477
Big time basketball player
owns him.

01:04:01.885 --> 01:04:04.979
That's Baffert and his wife
with Pioneer of the Nile.

01:04:06.055 --> 01:04:10.253
Won four graded
stakes in a row.
Been working real good.

01:04:11.961 --> 01:04:13.121
Who's that?

01:04:13.663 --> 01:04:18.100
That there's Jeff Mullins.
He trains I Want Revenge,
the favorite right now.

01:04:18.701 --> 01:04:21.499
Joe Talamo's riding him
in his first Derby.

01:04:22.639 --> 01:04:24.869
A billionaire from England
owns that one.

01:04:24.941 --> 01:04:26.408
Dunkirk.

01:04:27.076 --> 01:04:29.101
They paid almost
$4 million for him.

01:04:30.346 --> 01:04:34.248
Some sheik's horse
is next to us.
Regal Ransom.

01:04:37.187 --> 01:04:40.281
And here we are.
This is your new home, Bird.

01:04:58.308 --> 01:04:59.673
Good boy. (KISSING)

01:05:16.359 --> 01:05:18.520
Hey, who took my razor?

01:05:29.739 --> 01:05:31.263
Hey, Jerry, what's up?

01:05:31.341 --> 01:05:32.774
Good news, Calvin.
What's that?

01:05:32.842 --> 01:05:35.106
You're gonna ride Beethoven
in the Kentucky Derby.

01:05:35.178 --> 01:05:36.236
Serious?
Yeah.

01:05:36.312 --> 01:05:37.643
Thank you very much. Good job.

01:05:37.714 --> 01:05:39.238
Hey, guys,
I got my Derby horse!

01:05:39.315 --> 01:05:40.714
Hey, congratulations.
Thank you, John.

01:05:40.783 --> 01:05:42.580
Appreciate it very much, man.

01:05:42.652 --> 01:05:44.279
I appreciate it, Fabio.
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

01:05:44.354 --> 01:05:46.481
Thank you, my man,
appreciate it very much.

01:05:46.556 --> 01:05:47.853
Thank you for that, buddy.
Well done, Calvin.

