But this year,
this year we anticipate

01:23:19.641 --> 01:23:23.634
a crowd of more than 150,000!

01:23:23.712 --> 01:23:24.701
(CROWD APPLAUDING)

01:23:28.617 --> 01:23:30.847
We have owners
from all over the world
here tonight.

01:23:30.919 --> 01:23:34.912
Ireland, Dubai,
France, England.

01:23:35.424 --> 01:23:37.892
Oh... (CHUCKLING)
Even New Mexico!

01:23:37.959 --> 01:23:39.654
(CROWD LAUGHING)

01:23:51.039 --> 01:23:52.165
Good evening, Mr. Woolley.

01:23:52.307 --> 01:23:53.399
Evenin'.

01:23:53.475 --> 01:23:56.672
Charlie's on a coffee run
and Bird's been asking
for you.

01:23:57.346 --> 01:23:58.813
Need anything?

01:23:58.880 --> 01:24:01.644
Nah, I'm good. Thank you.

01:24:07.022 --> 01:24:10.583
Hey. How you doing, buddy?

01:24:13.628 --> 01:24:15.152
I want to thank you

01:24:16.531 --> 01:24:19.967
for taking us to the biggest
dance in the world, Bird.

01:24:22.571 --> 01:24:27.167
I never thought
in a million years
I'd ever be here.

01:24:29.911 --> 01:24:30.900
(EXHALING)

01:24:33.749 --> 01:24:35.842
Don't you worry
about tomorrow.

01:24:36.852 --> 01:24:38.843
You just run your race.

01:24:41.022 --> 01:24:45.584
And you show 'em how big
a heart you got. All right?

01:24:46.361 --> 01:24:47.658
(SNORTING)

01:25:51.660 --> 01:25:53.287
(SNORING)

01:26:00.902 --> 01:26:01.891
Ah!

01:26:02.838 --> 01:26:04.100
What the hell?

01:26:04.239 --> 01:26:05.467
Wake up, sunshine.

01:26:06.975 --> 01:26:08.340
It's showtime.

01:26:32.300 --> 01:26:34.996
(TV HOSTS TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

01:26:38.306 --> 01:26:39.796
Yup, Rachael Rice designed it.

01:26:39.875 --> 01:26:41.103
I don't wear suits anymore.

01:26:41.176 --> 01:26:42.165
I don't know if you can see me
under here.

01:27:02.964 --> 01:27:05.159
(PHONE RINGING)

01:27:09.371 --> 01:27:12.363
Gotcha. I'll tell him.

01:27:23.852 --> 01:27:25.046
Hey, guys.

01:27:26.421 --> 01:27:28.082
There's been a scratch
in the Derby.

01:27:32.160 --> 01:27:34.025
I Want Revenge is out.

01:27:35.096 --> 01:27:37.155
(ALL MURMURING)

01:27:44.573 --> 01:27:47.371
Sorry about that, buddy.
You'll get them
next year, all right?

01:27:47.442 --> 01:27:49.069
Don't worry about it.

01:27:54.583 --> 01:27:57.950
Looks good. Sam, could you put
your hand on your hips
like Joe's doing?

01:28:02.757 --> 01:28:06.090
...as is Godolphin Racing
all the way from Dubai
with two horses.

01:28:06.161 --> 01:28:08.356
Regal Ransom, Desert Party,

01:28:08.430 --> 01:28:11.263
Sheik Mohammed
Al Maktoum's trainer
Saeed Bin Suroor.

01:28:11.333 --> 01:28:14.166
Saeed, you guys have won
just about everything
there is to win in racing

01:28:14.235 --> 01:28:17.068
except the Derby.
What do you make
of your chances today?

01:28:17.138 --> 01:28:20.005
Both horses had a good flight
over and are training well.

01:28:20.075 --> 01:28:22.270
We wouldn't have come this far
if we did not expect to win.

01:28:22.344 --> 01:28:23.368
Best of luck, gentlemen.

01:28:25.447 --> 01:28:29.042
Trainer Chip Woolley,
you shattered your leg
less than five weeks ago,

01:28:29.117 --> 01:28:32.848
and here you are making
this long walk over with your
gelding, Mine That Bird.

01:28:32.921 --> 01:28:37.722
Everyone in racing wants
to make this walk
even on one leg.

01:28:37.792 --> 01:28:40.158
Feeling here's unlike
none other.

01:28:40.228 --> 01:28:43.197
Here? You realize
this is the Kentucky Derby

01:28:43.264 --> 01:28:44.697
and you guys are looking
like you're ready

01:28:44.766 --> 01:28:46.825
for the shoot out
at the O.K. Corral.

01:28:46.901 --> 01:28:48.459
Yeah, we're ready
for anything.

01:28:48.536 --> 01:28:49.901
Go get 'em, Chip.

01:28:51.072 --> 01:28:56.032
There's Hall of Fame trainer
Bob Baffert. Three time Derby
winning trainer Bob Baffert.

01:28:56.111 --> 01:28:58.909
We know how excited
you've been all week
about your colt,

01:28:58.980 --> 01:29:01.710
Pioneer of the Nile,
in this Derby. Why?

01:29:01.783 --> 01:29:05.446
Well, I haven't had
a legitimate Derby horse
in years.

01:29:05.520 --> 01:29:08.956
This guy's already won over
a million dollars,
he's training beautifully.

01:29:09.024 --> 01:29:12.118
Bob, competition-wise,
who do you fear the most?

01:29:12.193 --> 01:29:14.320
Well, I'm worried about all
of them.

01:29:15.397 --> 01:29:18.366
Well, maybe not the cowboys.
(CHUCKLING)

01:29:18.433 --> 01:29:19.764
Best of luck, Bob.

01:29:51.366 --> 01:29:54.130
(CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY)

01:29:57.505 --> 01:29:59.496
We made them ourselves.

01:29:59.574 --> 01:30:00.973
(LAUGHING)

01:30:05.780 --> 01:30:06.906
(LAUGHING)

01:30:09.818 --> 01:30:12.082
Hey, how you all doing?
All right?

01:30:12.153 --> 01:30:13.142
Hi. Good luck.

01:30:13.221 --> 01:30:14.210
It's all right? Good, good.

01:30:14.289 --> 01:30:15.950
Hey, man,
we're happy to have you.

01:30:16.024 --> 01:30:17.321
Thank you.
I appreciate it very much.

01:30:17.392 --> 01:30:20.327
Thank you so much.
How you all doing?
Good to meet you.

01:30:20.395 --> 01:30:21.862
Thank you. Good luck.

01:30:21.930 --> 01:30:23.397
Thank you,
I appreciate it very much.

01:30:24.232 --> 01:30:25.699
I'll try to get
the job done, okay?

01:30:25.767 --> 01:30:26.995
All right.

01:30:27.202 --> 01:30:30.968
Ah! How you doing, sir?
Things all right?
Good, Calvin.

01:30:31.039 --> 01:30:32.131
You all right?
Hey.

01:30:32.207 --> 01:30:33.231
Chip. How's everything?

01:30:33.308 --> 01:30:34.297
Good.

01:30:35.577 --> 01:30:39.377
There's plenty of speed
in here. So don't worry
if we're a little ways back.

01:30:39.447 --> 01:30:42.541
Just get a clean break
and keep him covered up.

01:30:42.617 --> 01:30:45.882
Once he sees daylight,
he's gone.

01:30:45.954 --> 01:30:47.114
You got it.

01:30:52.360 --> 01:30:54.453
All right, guys,
let's get lucky.

01:30:59.734 --> 01:31:03.363
Hell. There he goes.

01:31:06.875 --> 01:31:08.536
Hey, y'all listen up.

01:31:15.784 --> 01:31:18.014
I want to thank y'all
for all ya done.

01:31:19.220 --> 01:31:21.745
Bird couldn't have had
a better team.

01:31:24.626 --> 01:31:27.151
No matter what happens
out there

01:31:27.228 --> 01:31:30.220
I'm just glad
we're here together.

01:31:37.438 --> 01:31:39.406
This is the best day
of my life

01:31:42.944 --> 01:31:44.639
and I won't forget it.

01:31:48.349 --> 01:31:50.408
We done all we can,

01:31:50.485 --> 01:31:52.919
so what do you say we go
have us a great time, huh?

01:31:52.987 --> 01:31:54.579
(LAUGHING)

01:31:54.656 --> 01:31:56.886
Get in there.
Come on! Come on!

01:31:57.525 --> 01:31:59.288
(BAND PLAYING)

01:32:00.528 --> 01:32:07.457
♪ <i>The sun shines bright</i>
<i>on my old Kentucky home</i>

01:32:07.769 --> 01:32:12.763
♪ <i>'Tis summer,</i>
<i>the people are gay</i>

01:32:15.810 --> 01:32:20.372
♪ <i>By and by, hard times comes</i>

01:32:20.448 --> 01:32:23.611
♪ <i>A-knocking at the door</i>

01:32:23.685 --> 01:32:29.681
♪ <i>Then my old Kentucky home</i>
<i>good night</i>

01:32:31.392 --> 01:32:38.127
♪ <i>For the Old Kentucky</i>
<i>Home far away</i> ♪

01:32:39.868 --> 01:32:41.802
(CHEERING)

01:32:45.139 --> 01:32:49.838
We're just moments away from
the 135th running
of the Kentucky Derby.

01:32:49.911 --> 01:32:52.311
Friesan Fire,
the favorite at 7-to-2.

01:32:52.380 --> 01:32:54.177
Dunkirk, second choice
at 5-to-1

01:32:54.249 --> 01:32:58.083
and Bob Baffert's
Pioneer of the Nile,
third choice at 6-to-1.

01:32:58.386 --> 01:33:01.321
Now, some of the biggest
long shots on the tote board.

01:33:01.389 --> 01:33:03.584
Atomic Rain, Join in the Dance

01:33:03.658 --> 01:33:06.786
and at 50-to-1,
Mine That Bird.

01:33:07.028 --> 01:33:09.189
(WOMAN TALKING ON TV)

01:33:11.599 --> 01:33:12.793
Hey, Bill.

01:33:14.736 --> 01:33:16.636
I bet you Bird don't finish
in the top ten.

01:33:19.207 --> 01:33:20.333
How much you got?

01:33:22.844 --> 01:33:24.106
Twenty bucks.

01:33:26.014 --> 01:33:27.413
I'll take that bet.

01:33:29.017 --> 01:33:31.952
Anyone else think he won't
finish in the top ten?

01:33:32.020 --> 01:33:33.009
Huh?

01:33:33.755 --> 01:33:35.620
Put your money right here!

01:33:35.690 --> 01:33:36.679
I'm in.

01:33:36.758 --> 01:33:37.747
I'll take it.

01:33:38.293 --> 01:33:40.284
There you go. All right.

01:33:40.595 --> 01:33:42.324
That's it. Yeah.

01:33:42.397 --> 01:33:43.887
MAN: Double down on that.
Double down.

01:33:43.965 --> 01:33:46.263
Yeah, ladies. Thank you.

01:33:46.935 --> 01:33:49.597
Yeah. Look at that.

01:33:57.211 --> 01:33:58.508
Hey, uh, Alex?

01:33:58.646 --> 01:33:59.943
Yeah?

01:34:01.416 --> 01:34:04.442
I was... I was wondering.

01:34:04.519 --> 01:34:06.316
Wondering what, Chip?
They're about to go.

01:34:06.387 --> 01:34:08.218
No, I know.

01:34:08.289 --> 01:34:09.950
I was wondering if...

01:34:13.494 --> 01:34:16.463
If maybe you might consider
riding for me sometime.

01:34:18.399 --> 01:34:19.798
Like in a race?

01:34:21.102 --> 01:34:22.592
I could use a good jockey.

01:34:24.072 --> 01:34:25.232
Oh, my God.

01:34:26.674 --> 01:34:28.471
Oh, my God.

01:34:31.946 --> 01:34:33.277
Thank you.

01:34:35.783 --> 01:34:36.943
Thank you so much.

01:34:37.085 --> 01:34:38.245
Okay, okay.

01:34:38.920 --> 01:34:38.953
(BELL RINGING)

01:34:38.953 --> 01:34:40.944
(BELL RINGING)

01:34:50.164 --> 01:34:52.564
All right, number 12.
He's an easy loader, guys.

01:34:52.700 --> 01:34:55.100
Come on, boys.
Now, 14's up,
let's bring him in.

01:35:14.722 --> 01:35:16.189
Please, God,

01:35:18.226 --> 01:35:20.353
just don't let him be last.

01:35:28.002 --> 01:35:29.060
How many now, Bob? Two out?

01:35:29.203 --> 01:35:30.261
Two left.

01:35:34.742 --> 01:35:36.733
Come on, Bird. Come on.

01:35:48.790 --> 01:35:50.951
(ANNOUNCER):
<i>They're in the gate.</i>
(STARTER PISTOL FIRING)

01:35:51.025 --> 01:35:54.756
<i>And they're off</i>
<i>in the Kentucky Derby!</i>

01:35:57.698 --> 01:36:00.166
<i>And it's Join in the Dance</i>
<i>racing for the lead.</i>

01:36:00.234 --> 01:36:01.997
<i>Musket Man has some</i>
<i>early speed on the inside.</i>

01:36:02.070 --> 01:36:04.129
<i>Here's Regal Ransom</i>
<i>with some speed as well.</i>

01:36:05.006 --> 01:36:07.167
Hey! We got mugged.

01:36:07.241 --> 01:36:09.175
What the hell was that?
Did you see that?

01:36:09.944 --> 01:36:12.606
<i>Beneath the Twin Spires for</i>
<i>the first time Regal Ransom</i>

01:36:12.680 --> 01:36:14.614
<i>and Join in the Dance</i>
<i>will vie for the early lead.</i>

01:36:14.682 --> 01:36:16.172
<i>Pioneer of the Nile</i>
<i>is right up there.</i>

01:36:16.250 --> 01:36:17.945
He got run over.

01:36:18.019 --> 01:36:20.613
<i>And that's Papa Clem down</i>
<i>toward the inside.</i>
<i>He's now fourth.</i>

01:36:20.688 --> 01:36:23.851
<i>Desert Party forwardly placed,</i>
<i>fifth on the outside.</i>

01:36:24.559 --> 01:36:27.153
<i>One mile remaining here in</i>
<i>the Run for the Roses,</i>

01:36:27.228 --> 01:36:29.423
<i>and the two long shot</i>
<i>leaders remain.</i>

01:36:31.365 --> 01:36:34.698
Flying Private is sixth,
Friesan Fire in and among
horses is now seventh.

01:36:34.769 --> 01:36:38.762
Musket Man is eighth,
Dunkirk is ninth
on the outside.

01:36:39.740 --> 01:36:41.332
He's last.

01:36:41.409 --> 01:36:44.970
ANNOUNCER: <i>Then farther back</i>
<i>down on the rail,</i>
<i>that is Atomic Rain</i>

01:36:45.046 --> 01:36:47.514
<i>running in the eleventh</i>
<i>position, two lengths back.</i>

01:36:47.582 --> 01:36:49.049
<i>And General Quarters</i>
<i>is now twelfth.</i>

01:36:49.117 --> 01:36:51.585
<i>Nowhere to Hide is thirteenth</i>
<i>on the outside.</i>

01:36:51.652 --> 01:36:54.780
<i>And 1 lengths behind the rest</i>
<i>of the field</i>
<i>is Mine That Bird.</i>

01:37:00.461 --> 01:37:03.328
<i>West Side Bernie is now</i>
<i>down toward the rail.</i>

01:37:03.397 --> 01:37:05.558
<i>And then on the outside</i>
<i>at the back of the pack</i>

01:37:05.633 --> 01:37:08.500
<i>beginning to move up now</i>
<i>is Hold Me Back.</i>

01:37:08.569 --> 01:37:10.799
<i>Advice is also back there</i>
<i>toward the back of the pack</i>

01:37:10.872 --> 01:37:13.966
<i>along with Chocolate Candy,</i>
<i>Summer Bird, Advice,</i>

01:37:14.041 --> 01:37:16.271
<i>and the last of them</i>
<i>all is Mr. Hot Stuff.</i>

01:37:16.344 --> 01:37:19.836
<i>So, down the backstretch run,</i>
<i>well behind the rest of them,</i>

01:37:19.914 --> 01:37:22.075
<i>is Mine That Bird.</i>

01:37:22.150 --> 01:37:25.142
Looks like we're going
the wrong way.

01:37:30.124 --> 01:37:33.651
<i>So down the backstretch run,</i>
<i>and Join in the Dance,</i>

01:37:33.728 --> 01:37:35.593
<i>an impudent</i>
<i>long-shot leader here,</i>

01:37:35.663 --> 01:37:37.460
<i>taking the field through</i>
<i>an opening half-mile</i>

01:37:37.532 --> 01:37:40.296
<i>that was strong,</i>
<i>47 and one-fifth seconds.</i>

01:37:42.537 --> 01:37:44.004
He's 30 lengths back.

01:37:45.072 --> 01:37:46.539
Maybe it's the mud.

01:37:46.607 --> 01:37:48.040
ANNOUNCER: <i>On the outside,</i>
<i>Pioneerof the Nile.</i>

01:37:48.109 --> 01:37:50.600
<i>Now, Garrett Gomez asking him</i>
<i>for a bit more.</i>
<i>He's right there.</i>

01:37:50.678 --> 01:37:52.373
Yes! Yes! Yeah, baby!

01:37:52.513 --> 01:37:54.208
Whoo!

01:37:55.383 --> 01:37:57.943
ANNOUNCER: <i>Papa Clem threads</i>
<i>his way through horses,</i>
<i>from sixth.</i>

01:37:58.019 --> 01:37:59.884
<i>Now Musket Man is now seventh.</i>

01:37:59.954 --> 01:38:04.414
<i>Chocolate Candy is beginning</i>
<i>to come alive now and</i>
<i>he's eighth on the outside.</i>

01:38:04.492 --> 01:38:06.426
All right, little Bird man,
let's go.

01:38:07.295 --> 01:38:11.095
Look at this. We might
actually beat someone.

01:38:11.632 --> 01:38:14.624
<i>Behind the far turn,</i>
<i>Join in the Dance</i>
<i>a narrow lead.</i>

01:38:14.702 --> 01:38:18.468
<i>Regal Ransom is pressing hard</i>
<i>and there goes</i>
<i>Pioneer of the Nile.</i>

01:38:18.539 --> 01:38:21.736
<i>Pioneer of the Nile</i>
<i>is making his advance</i>
<i>in the...</i>

01:38:21.809 --> 01:38:23.936
Eighth or ninth
would be all right.

01:38:28.683 --> 01:38:29.809
(KNOCKING)

01:38:29.884 --> 01:38:32.409
Mine That Bird! Hey!

01:38:32.486 --> 01:38:34.477
Mine That Bird,
he's coming up the rail!

01:38:34.555 --> 01:38:35.920
Where'd he go? I lost him.

01:38:36.057 --> 01:38:37.388
He can't get through.

01:38:37.491 --> 01:38:41.154
ANNOUNCER: <i>Then down toward</i>
<i>the rail, it's Advice,</i>
<i>as the field turns for home.</i>

01:38:41.229 --> 01:38:44.858
<i>Top of the stretch, it's still</i>
<i>Join in the Dance</i>
<i>with a tenuous lead.</i>

01:38:44.932 --> 01:38:48.231
<i>Regal Ransom</i>
<i>and Pioneer of the Nile</i>
<i>strike the front,</i>

01:38:48.302 --> 01:38:50.532
<i>just outside the eighth pole.</i>

01:38:50.605 --> 01:38:53.438
Fourth. Fourth would be good.

01:38:53.507 --> 01:38:55.532
Mine That Bird! Hey!

01:39:05.419 --> 01:39:08.252
(CHEERING)

01:39:08.823 --> 01:39:10.791
He's in the lead!
He's in the lead!
What? Where?

01:39:10.858 --> 01:39:13.793
Coming on through,
that is Mine That Bird now

01:39:13.861 --> 01:39:15.055
<i>who's coming on</i>
<i>to take the lead</i>

01:39:15.129 --> 01:39:16.926
<i>as they come down</i>
<i>to the finish!</i>

01:39:16.998 --> 01:39:18.522
(CHEERING)

01:39:18.599 --> 01:39:19.725
Whoo!

01:39:19.800 --> 01:39:22.860
ANNOUNCER: <i>Calvin Borel</i>
<i>in the saddle,</i>
<i>saluting the crowd!</i>

01:39:22.937 --> 01:39:25.337
Let him roll, Calvin!
Let him roll! Let him roll!

01:39:25.406 --> 01:39:26.498
No!

01:39:26.574 --> 01:39:28.007
ANNOUNCER: <i>...a hundred</i>
<i>and twenty thousand.</i>

01:39:28.075 --> 01:39:31.135
<i>Long, impossible long shot!</i>

01:39:31.212 --> 01:39:35.581
<i>Mine That Bird going to win</i>
<i>the Kentucky Derby</i>

01:39:35.650 --> 01:39:39.347
<i>in a spectacular,</i>
<i>spectacular upset.</i>

01:39:39.720 --> 01:39:44.453
Mine That Bird has won
the Kentucky Derby.
An impossible result here!

01:39:44.525 --> 01:39:45.617
Yeah! Whoo!

01:39:45.693 --> 01:39:48.218
God! Praise God! Oh, my gosh!

01:39:48.629 --> 01:39:51.655
We just won this
son-of-a-bitch!
Oh, my gosh!

01:39:51.732 --> 01:39:53.859
(CHEERING)

01:39:55.169 --> 01:39:56.932
(CHEERING)

01:40:00.308 --> 01:40:02.299
(SCREAMING)

01:40:03.144 --> 01:40:04.406
Let's go, let's go.

01:40:05.313 --> 01:40:07.338
Oh! Oh.

01:40:18.926 --> 01:40:21.724
(CROWD CHEERING)

01:40:24.732 --> 01:40:26.632
(CHEERING)

01:40:35.142 --> 01:40:36.439
How do we get down there?
I don't know.

01:40:36.510 --> 01:40:38.068
How do we get
to the winner's circle?

01:40:38.145 --> 01:40:39.772
I think it's down here.

01:40:40.214 --> 01:40:41.579
(CHUCKLING)

01:40:42.216 --> 01:40:43.649
You just said I love you
to whom?

01:40:43.718 --> 01:40:45.083
My momma and daddy.

01:40:45.219 --> 01:40:46.584
Who are no longer with us.

01:40:46.654 --> 01:40:49.953
I wish they were here.
Oh, Lord.
(SOBBING)

01:40:51.325 --> 01:40:54.624
If they'd only be here
to see what I accomplished
in my life.

